The NGX_HTTP_HANDLERSOCKET_JSON_MODULE is port to MySQL data by HandlerSocket https://github.com/ahiguti/HandlerSocket-Plugin-for-MySQL for fast http server nginx (http://nginx.org). 


INSTALLATION

You must to configure with arguments: --add-module=/full/path/to/dir/nginx_http_handlersocket_json_module and make & sudo make install.


CONFIG

The Config directives use in the location context.

Example

location ~ /cities/(.+)/$ {
		hs_json; 		# enable module

		 hs_json_host 		127.0.0.1;	# connection 127.0.0.1 
		 hs_json_port 		9998;		# and port 9998 default

		 hs_json_db		test;		# the db name
		 hs_json_table		city;		# the tablename

		 hs_json_index		name;		 # index name, the PRIMARY id default
 		 hs_json_fields		name,id;         # the output fieldlist

		 hs_json_op		"="; 		# "=" default operation 
		 hs_json_limit		10; 		# default is 10

		set $hs_request $1;			$ the set source input data 
	}


The output example:

curl http://localhost/cities/san/
[{"name":"San Amaro", "id": "12"},{"name":"San Andreas", "id": "13"},{"name":"San Andrs", "id": "14"} ... ]

LIMITATION

The limit output data is 1K. You can to increase the volume of output data of change the BUFF_SIZE define directive.

You can to use only one parameter of index search.